Type

public Type(java.lang.String image,
            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.Set<java.lang.String>> hierarchy)
Creates a new type with a specific image and type hierachy.

Parameters:
image - the image of the type.
hierarchy - the type hierachy.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if image == null or hierarchy == null.
TypingException - if the type hierarchy specified is not consistant. A type hierarchy is consistant if it does not contain cycle and all types inherite from object except the primitive type number.
